Charles MASHUNKASHEY, an Incompetent Person, by Fred S. Clinton, as Guardian, etc., v. UNITED STATES of America et al. No. 1927. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. June 27, 1939. No appearance for appellant. Whit Y. Mauzy, U. S. Atty., of Tulsa, Okl., for appellees.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed at appellant’s clerk’s costs, for failure to prosecute.
